<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>PriceCast · About the team</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/base.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/about.css">
  </head>
  <body class="pc-body pc-body--dark">
    <%= ECR.render("views/partials/_navbar.ecr") %>

    <main class="pc-main pc-main--about">
      <section class="pc-section-header pc-section-header--about">
        <h1 class="pc-section-title">About the PriceCast team</h1>
        <p class="pc-section-subtitle">
          A small project built for our course, combining MTGJSON, data processing,
          and a Crystal/Kemal web frontend.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="pc-about-layout">
        <article class="pc-about-card">
          <h2 class="pc-about-name">Your Name Here</h2>
          <div class="pc-about-role">Data pipeline · Model implementation · Frontend wiring</div>
          <p class="pc-about-text">
            Short bio goes here. For example: I'm a CS student interested in systems,
            data, and games. For PriceCast, I focused on building the data processing
            scripts, the linear regression pipeline, and wiring up the web views.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="pc-about-card">
          <h2 class="pc-about-name">Groupmate Name Here</h2>
          <div class="pc-about-role">MTG domain expertise · Design · Analysis</div>
          <p class="pc-about-text">
            Short bio goes here. For example: I'm a long-time MTG player with a focus
            on Commander and Modern. For PriceCast, I helped select demo cards, think
            about meaningful features, and shape how we explain the results.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="pc-footer pc-footer--dark">
      <div class="pc-footer-inner">
        <span>PriceCast · MTG price demo</span>
        <span class="pc-footer-tags">
          Built by our team for course credit. Not financial advice.
        </span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
